  final p1 = Person()
    ..name = "Alice"
    ..age = 25
    ..address = "123 Main St";
  p1.printDetails();
}
```

In this example, we've added custom setter methods for each of the instance variables: name, age, and address. Each setter method includes a print statement that shows which setter has been called.

In the main function, we are creating a new instance of the Person class using the default constructor which does not take any parameters. Then we use the cascade operator to set the values of the three instance variables of the object, one after the other. 

```
